reviews.text: Visiting from a North American city with lots of immigrants from Shanghai and Shanghai restaurants. Hoping for a better experience in Asia but was disappointed. The onion pancake was dried  and crumbling; the steam plain bun has some dried dough in the middle. I think the kitchen didn't prep the dough for that day. The noodle was ok. The best dish is their Xiaolongbao.

Located in the basement of Star House. Large restaurant but still very crowded. Long lines during lunch and dinner traffic. Restaurant staff very helpful.  I like the steamed dumpling the most - thin wrap with juicy, soft and tender meat! Reasonably priced.

One of the best restaurants in Tsim Sha Tsui!! There is always a queue here and please expect some waiting time. The ambiance is cool and service is super good. Most of the dishes I tried out were amazing. I would recommend the Wontons here, they were simply stunning 😋 I do recommend this place for people looking for Shanghai style food.
Yummy!!! But the dishes are a bit too oily!!

Food is alright not the greatest. During ordering my food the waiter said that the dish would be small... but I didn’t expect a soup would be the size of a cup... when the picture was a large bowl. Their Xiao long bao is ok though. The server was pretty aggressive to customers.

reviews.text:
老牌商廈，含商場及寫字樓。
亦有幾間美心集團食館及誠品店。地下有麥當奴漢堡飽店。
鄰近天星碼頭，腳程五分鐘可達香港文化中心及香港太空館，廿分鐘可步行至科學舘。
星光行 位於尖沙咀碼頭傍邊 商場面積吾算中型 但冇咩野行 樓上主要是寫字樓 有學聯 有出名的北京樓 但不是人人食得起 場內大部份店舖壽命不長 浪費了－個非常方便之商業地段 ！
觀光旅遊區，頗受遊客歡迎。

Visiting from a North American city with lots of immigrants from Shanghai and Shanghai restaurants. Hoping for a better experience in Asia but was disappointed. The onion pancake was dried  and crumbling; the steam plain bun has some dried dough in the middle. I think the kitchen didn't prep the dough for that day. The noodle was ok. The best dish is their Xiaolongbao.

Located in the basement of Star House. Large restaurant but still very crowded. Long lines during lunch and dinner traffic. Restaurant staff very helpful.  I like the steamed dumpling the most - thin wrap with juicy, soft and tender meat! Reasonably priced.

One of the best restaurants in Tsim Sha Tsui!! There is always a queue here and please expect some waiting time. The ambiance is cool and service is super good. Most of the dishes I tried out were amazing. I would recommend the Wontons here, they were simply stunning 😋 I do recommend this place for people looking for Shanghai style food.
Yummy!!! But the dishes are a bit too oily!!

Food is alright not the greatest. During ordering my food the waiter said that the dish would be small... but I didn’t expect a soup would be the size of a cup... when the picture was a large bowl. Their Xiao long bao is ok though. The server was pretty aggressive to customers.
服務生態度良好
가격대비 맛이 별로임. 짬뽕 같은 음식을 먹었는데 한국 입맛엔 안맞음. 고수가 많이들어감. 튀김 만두는 좋으나 가격이 비쌈. 일행중 병맥주를 시켰는데 김 빠진 맥주였음.
여기 가격도 좋고 맛도 괜찮아요 분위기도 현지인들 많고요. 그러니까 평점 좋게 주지마세요 아는 사람만 올수 있게 ㅋㅋ
지하1층에 있습니다. 홍콩에서 먹은 딤섬중 여기 딤섬이 가장 맛있었습니다. 탄탄면은 제가 시킨건 좀 별로였습니다.

우연히 들렸는데 맛있었습니다.
가격 나쁘지 않고 직원들도 친절해서 2번 방문했습니다. 10프로의 서비스 차지 붙어요.

delicious food with good service quality. not very expensive but there is 10percentage service charges in the bill.
